Put stuff on the field, link summon, put more stuff on the field, Xyz summon, put more stuff on the field, etc. Your major playmaker is Swap Frog, which has three effects, a special summoning effect, a foolish burial effect, and a self bounce effect that also gives you another normal summon. you can pair Swap Frog with Inferno Reckless Summon to bring out two more, but because of timing you have to activate IRS on the summon of Swap, so you only activate the two you summon, since Swap Frog is a "when" effect, instead of an "if". This deck also has super easy access to Toadally Awesome, possibly the best Xyz monster in the game, and definitely the best rank 2.

deck_excerpt: ABC meta oriented deck Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bgSm9M8WXnM&feature=youtu.be
deck_description: Gameplay of the deck : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bgSm9M8WXnM&feature=youtu.be     Here is an ABC deck built to perform against meta with some techs that increase it's stability, defensive abilities and OTK potential. The basics like gadgets and Galaxy Soldier are still here to start the same loops that the classic builds.   So the specific cards you'll find are : The Psy-Frame package, that is usefull to negate an Ash Blossom targetting a draw card or Terraforming/Union Hangar to have 2 monsters to start boards pretty effectively, or just use Psy-Frame Lambda's ability to negate cards during your opponent's turn to add disruption to your established board. Note that they are light attribute and are potential targets for Galaxy Soldier's effect. The Sky Striker package is really good in this deck sinse it can search out multiple Sky Striker cards and cycle the deck when having good effects to handle the opponent's board. Kagari is a machine monster and can be used to summon Platinum Gadget. With Sky Striker Mecha - Shark Canon and Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor you can handle annoying monsters in the graveyard or in the field like Plasma Destiny Hero, and steal opponent's monsters to rapidly gain access to Avramax and Borrelsword for OTK strategies. Monster Gate can deblock hands by sending somme letters to the graveyard that would trigger summoning or searching effects and can bring out monsters like Silver Gadget or Gold Gadget to spam the board and gain access to ABC Dragon Buster even with a bricky hand. Note that you can send spells to the graveyard and instantly gain acces to the full power effects of the Sky Striker cards. Twin Twisters are Added main deck to send a needed letter to the graveyard and break backrow cards and floodgates that could stop the deck in some situations. The extra deck is quite generic, we Simply run a Gear Gigant X to search the last letters for the summoning of ABC Dragon Buster, and Crusadia Equimax to have a simple way to summon Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax with the Sky Striker combos or bypass the biggest beatsticks and potentially gain access to simple OTKs.   The side deck : Dark Ruler No More is a great card against combo decks like Guardragons and won't be negated by Mystical Beasts monsters from Pendulum decks, it's also a spell card so it will allow us to triger the full power effect of Sky Striker cards more easilly. Sky Striker Maneuver - Afterburners is an alternative way to handle monsters and is a safe way to break through monsters that prevent special summons like Vanity Fiend or monsters with annoying disruption effects to start our loops, it is searchable by Engage. Fantastical Dragon Phantazmay is a good way to draw cards when going second against decks like Orcust, and can pressure opponent's play that set monsters with disruption effects The artifact package is an excellent option to lock combo decks when going first with Artifact Scythe and can stop Orcust and Thunder Dragon with Artifact Lancea. Lastly Anti-Spell Fragrance is a way to shut down Sky Striker and Pendulum when going first and won't be a problem after we set our board.

deck_name: Just Your Everyday Fairytale | Legend Of Heart
deck_excerpt: Legendary Dragons, Legendary Knights, and weird fusion things
deck_description: TIMEEEEEEEAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAS!!!!!!!!!

Dino's aren't the most competetive deck to play right now but surely are a lot fun. They don't make the most impressive boards but can make some that easily win you the game (They also have a OTK, for those who want). This Dino deck really depends on going second and going first with the wrong cards in your hand can hurt sometimes.  Lost World Dino is one of my favorite decks and I will show you why. Dino's have a very simple strategy; putting big beatsticks and negates on the board. This is mostly possible with ULTIMATE CONDUCTER TYRANNO, the EVOLZAR duo and PANKRATOPS. The main plays start with OVIRAPTOR and a combination of MISCELLANEOUSAURUS and/or LOST WORLD in your hand, this is why you play 3 FOSSIL DIG to search you combo starters. I play 6 handtraps to disrupt opponents plays and 2 to get rid of powerfull boss monsters.  The OTK is having an token on your opponents field with LOST WORLD (OTK is still possible without token, you opponent just needs a monster on their side of the field), getting DUGARES on the board with UCT, activating DUGARES's effect to double UCT's attack, linking DUGARES and another card away for PENTESTAG (that points to UCT), destroy a monster in your hand to change your opponents monsters to face down defense position, attack every monster with UCT for 7000 piercing dmg (and directly after all monsters are gone.  Any questions can be send to me, will do my best to answer them quickly.  Thank you and have fun playing!

deck_excerpt: A Malefic deck with two win conditions
deck_description: This deck has two win conditions. The first one is a standard beatdown focused playstyle with Malefic Stardust/Malefic Territory to protect Malefic world. In ~80% of starting hands you will have either 1 Malefic World or 1 Malefic Territory (terrraforming but better).  The second win condition of this deck is to sit on Mathmech Processor Final Sigma in the extra monster zone with a skill drain on field. To summon Final Sigma all you need is either: Malefic Parallel Gear + Cyber End Dragon OR Malefic Paradox Gear + Malefic World/Malefic Territory. Conbined with Skill Drain, Final Sigma will be extremely hard to out for the opponent (assuming no Kaijus)

deck_excerpt: Traptrix and Mekk-Knights in a deck together
deck_description: The idea behind this deck is to not only give your Mekk-knight monsters some okay going first plays but also to stun out your opponent by using the Trap Hole and Traptrix cards. Any hand that opens with at least 1 Mekk, 1 Traptrix, and 1 spell/trap is capable of creating a somewhat strong opening board.  Going first your best bet is to establish a column by turning any main deck Traptrix monster into Sera and using any spell/trap to create an opening for your Mekk-knights to be summoned. Once you've done most of your Mekk-knight plays, you can either turn any level 4s on the field into a Traptrix Rafflesia or a Time Theif Redoer or using 3 cards to create BLS - Soldier of Chaos. This deck is capable of opening only monsters or only spell/traps, but it is usually a healthy mix of both.  The best hand I've experienced with this deck was:  Myrmeleo, Purple Nightfall, Kagetokage, Shade Brigandine, and Secret.

deck_excerpt: My take on an effective Salamangreats deck for the November 2019 format
deck_description: This deck makes use of salamangreats' ability to use multiple hand traps to hinder the opponent while setting up a strong stun to hinder their plays turn 1. Going first you can go 1 of 2 ways: 1) If you know your facing a Nibiru, make Apollousa by 5th summon. You can use will, archiver, and your natural extenders to do this. 2) If you know there's no nibiru, just perform the standard salamangreat combo, you should be able to end on 2 negates on field and at least 1 hand trap in the hand for 3 disruptions. Ghost belle is a very strong hand trap this format, being able to hit every one of the top decks. Orcust- stops cymbal skeleton and Yellow Martin for the LunaLight build. Strikers- Stops raye and kagari. Salamangreats- what doesn't it stop? Thunder- Stops hawk preventing the thunder player from extending combo.     The side deck is more diverse able to handle a wider variety of decks. Red reboot would be your flex spot, if you feel like adding a 3rd twin twisters or another sanctum feel free. You'll notice no nibiru, this is because nibiru isn't really as strong as you'd believe right now. Its a blow-out vs rogue decks but hurts the meta decks very little. If you disagree, you're welcome to experiment with it, I feel its a waste of space better used for more effective hand traps or stun cards like the artifact package. I have included trap trick in the side deck as a 3rd sanctum. The idea behind this is that trap trick is a way to thin 2 cards from your deck upon activation. Even if you open with sanctum and trap trick, you can use the card to grab an impermanence and thin 2 cards from your deck and increase consistency.

deck_excerpt: HERO it's comming... and it's very strong deck.
deck_description:
HERO é um arquétipo de cards do Yu-Gi-Oh! no qual, eu mais amo nesse jogo! Desde Yu-Gi-Oh!GX, quando o Jaden Yuki invocava aquelas lindas fusões clássicas, sempre tive um enorme desejo em fazer esse deck, ao qual, admiro muito. Bem, pra quem não sabe, o deck gira em torno de monstros do tipo guerreiro, dos mais variados atributos, que envolve principalmente invocação do deck extra de monstros fusão, sendo eles definidos nas seguintes tipos de HERO:
  • Herói Elementar
  • Herói do Destino
  • Herói Mascarado
  • Herói da Visão
  • Herói Maléfico
  • Neospacial
  • Herói Xtra
E bem, e a mecânica do deck é até que muito boa, no qual você busca as suas matérias de fusão e pelos mais variados efeitos, busca meios de usa-las para trazer seus HEROS mais fortes. E por muito tempo, o deck foi bem abalado, tendo a carta "Um Herói Vive" limitada, e só recentemente, o Herói do Elemento Stratos saiu completamente da banlist, após quase 5 anos banido/limitada, e claro, o Herói do Destino - Malicioso, que com mais uma cópia, te dá acesso a mais combos e monstros a serem trazidos. O seu campo Core, é sempre passar o turno, se for você quem começa, com um Herói Destino - Plasma, que nega todos os efeitos de monstros de face pra cima no campo do oponente, uma habilidade extremamente forte, forçando seu oponente a ter que interagir com você e gastar recursos, e mais um monstro para se dar a Mudar a Máscara, que vai ser setada e utilizada no turno do oponente, com o objetivo de trazer a Lei Negra, o Herói Mascarado, que todas as cartas do oponente são banidas em vez de ir pro cemitério, e claro, a sua habilidade de que se o oponente adiciona cartas na mão do deck, ele descartar uma carta, o que faz o seu oponente perder ainda mais recursos. Também pode se por um Herói do Destino - Distopia sendo apontado pelo Herói Xtra Dizimador Horrífico, que aumenta o atk dele e de monstros HERO em suas zonas em 100 pra cada HERO de nome diferente no cemitério, e claro, Distopia destrói qualquer carta no turno de qualquer jogador, contanto que ele esteja com o atk alterado, o que é sempre bom ter em mãos, o Neos Honesto, para dar muito atk as seus HEROS, servindo tanto para bater no seu oponente, como para defender seus HEROS. E como jogando por segundo, fazendo os mais variados combos para trazer o Herói Elementar Sunriser que te dá acesso à Fusão Miraculosa, podendo assim trazer o Herói Elementar Zero Absoluto usando o Herói Elementar Liquidman e outro Herói Elementar, para se dar uma Mudar a Máscara no Zero Absoluto, com o objetivo de "triggar" os efeitos do Zero Absoluto e o Herói Mascarado Acid,  que, quando Zero Absoluto saí do campo ele destrói todos os monstros do oponente, "trigga" o efeito do Acid, que quando entra no campo, destrói todas as cartas mágicas e armadilhas do oponente, deixando o campo livre para um OTK, sendo para mim, um dos combos mais fortes dos HEROS. O deck ainda irá receber os futuros suportes, mas o que já se percebe, que o deck de HERO chegou chegando, e vai causar bastante barulho, muito certamente.

deck_excerpt: Heraldry Crest is ready for action!
deck_description: Vetrix, known as Tron in the Japanese and Italian versions and born Byron Arclight, is a character appearing in the Yu-Gi-Oh! ZEXAL anime. He appears as the secondary antagonist during the World Duel Carnival arc. Vetrix was formerly involved with Dr. Faker's business, and has sworn to take revenge alongside his sons: Trey, Quattro and Quinton. After Trey was defeated by Yuma Tsukumo, he made plans to target him as well since he possessed the "Original Number". Though his appearance is that of a child younger than the rest of the Vetrix Family, he is their father. He was betrayed by Dr. Faker, who used him and Kazuma Tsukumo as sacrifices to open the door to another dimension. When he returned, his form was mutated into that of a child. Vetrix plays a "Heraldic" Deck, composed of cards focused on control and manipulation, including the "Heraldic Beasts" and a line-up of "Heraldry" Spell/Trap Cards. His main strategy involves swarm tactics through cards such as "Heraldic Beast Eale" and "Heraldry Reborn" so he can easily Xyz Summon his "Number" monsters. Several of his "Heraldic Beasts" also generate card advantages by banishing themselves from his Graveyard.

deck_name: Prank-Kids Invoked ft. Thunder Dragon November 2019
deck_excerpt: Prank-Kids with multiple Fusions and disruptions.
deck_description:
The main objective of the deck is to get a Colossus or Toadally Awesome for negations/lockdown. Also, it is capable to make Prank-Kids Battle Butler or Invoked Mechaba (if you end up with 1 of 2 main archetypes). A few notes for you:
  • Prank-Kids monsters: To swarm the deck and to have enough resources for Battle Butler. Notes: Prank-Kids Fansies should send Prank-Kids Plan to recycle those Prank-Kids. When you use Prank-Kids Rocksies effect, you should banish those Thunder Dragon cards to get access to Thunder Dragon Fusion (then make Battle Butler with it) or to refresh hand with Thunder Dragonhawk (in case your hand is bad).
  • Prank-Kids Pandemonium should only be used in your last step or your opponent's turn since it locks you in Prank-Kids monsters.
  • Magical Meltdown has better protection to your Fusion monsters, so if you have both Field Spell, activate Magical Meltdown after Prank-Kids Place.
  • If you want to make Invoked Mechaba, you should use either: Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit/ Thunder Dragonhawk / opponent monsters in the GY (especially Effect Veiler) or you can make Reprodocus to change the Attribute of monsters it points to LIGHT.
  • Thunder Dragon Fusion is mainly for shuffling back materials for Prank-Kids Battle Butler, so to make Thunder Dragon Colossus, you can banish Thunder Dragonroar to bring out Thunder Dragondark, then send it to the GY (you can do it by linking it with another monster for Reprodocus) to search Thunder Dragon Fusion. You can have Colossus by using Hawk (if you have one) to resurrect Roar then Contact Fusion.
  • Last but not least, by using Prank-Kids Special Summons, you can bring out Toadally Awesome by 2 Prank-Kids Dropsies, adding an extra layer to your disruptions.
Thank you for reading this, and if you have any questions, comment below!

deck_excerpt: Dark Zane’s deck from Yu-Gi-Oh! World Championship 2008 NDS game.
deck_description: In World Championship 2008, Dark Zane plays a deck titled "Underworld Deck".

Pure Galaxy-Eyes Deck (Post October 2019 Banlist)

This updated Galaxy-Eyes deck is mainly for bringing out Xyz monsters, such as Galaxy-Eyes Photon lord and Cyber Dragon Infinity, which can negate and distrupt your opponents turn.

The Deck:
  • Main Deck(Monsters) -
    • Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon(x3)
      • This card is at 3 as you want to see it in your hand to combo with Galaxy soldier in your hand. You also want to see it as it can battle monsters that cant be destroyed by battle, by instead banishing them for the phase.
    • Galaxy Knight(x2)
      • This is at 2 because you dont want to see it in your hand as much due to it being a brick. You want to search this card from the effect of Galaxy Soldier (you should discard Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon for the effect of Galaxy Soldier). This card does take up a normal summon from you but in return can summon another level 8 for you to go into your XYZ monsters.
    • Galaxy Soldier(x3)
      • One of the best cards in the main deck as it allows you discard a card to special summon itself and search a "Galaxy" monster. This card will generally be summoned by discarding Galaxy-Eyes Photon dragon to search Galaxy Knight, assuming that you have not normal summoned prior to Galaxy Soldiers special summon. Having more than 2 Galaxy Soldiers can also result in you summoning Cyber Dragon Infinity.
    • Galaxy Wizard(x3)
      • This card is your main normal summon and a great card for searching and setting up. This card can also turn into a level 8 thus helping you with your XYZ summons. Futhermore if able to summon this card, with Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon in the GY and Photon Vanisher or and other body on the field, then you can tribute Galaxy Wizard and search Galaxy Trance which you can make Galaxy-Eyes Solflare Dragon with Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord. On your opponents turn you can search Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon via Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lords second effect. This gives you two distruptions on the field and and other such as Tachyon Transmigration.
    • Photon Orbital(x3)
      • Now we get into cards which are mainly used for utility. This card just gives a free search which this deck likes. This card can also be used as Galaxy Soldier's discarder or Galaxy-Eyes Solflare Dragon's discarder.
    • Photon Vanisher(x3)
      • This card allows the deck to basically get a free Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon in your hand. This helps alot and can even be used to special summon Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon or Galaxy-Eyes Solflare Dragon. This card can be used as discard material.
  • Main Deck(Spells) -
    • Accellight(x1)
      • Acts as the 4th copy of Galaxy wizard and shall only be used for the purpose. (That's how good Galaxy Wizard is in this deck).
    • Galaxy Expedition(x3)
      • This card Extends your plays and I just cant see why you wont run 3 of this. This card and Galaxy Wizard is a free Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord.
    • Galaxy Trance(x2)
      • This card is EXTREMELY GOOD but we only run two because it's a card you want to search off Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord as a way to get an XYZ monster after your opponent destroys all your cards (if they do). The card can also be bricky as you may have no way to send Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon to the GY.
    • Monster reborn(x1)
      • Extender.
    • Photon Sanctuary(x3)
      • A free Galaxy-Eyes Solflare Dragon, allowing you to summon more XYZ monsters from the Extra Deck
    • Return Of The Dragon Lords(x3)
      • A better monster reborn as it protects your Link and XYZ monsters
    • Trade-In(x3)
      • Pot of Greed is banned and this card allows you to get your Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon from your hand to the GY. If you bricked and you have Trade-In, Photon Vanisher and a card you can normal summon, it will make you refresh your hand with some bodies on the field.
    • Galaxy Zero(x1)
      • You can summon XYZ monsters for free and the XYZ summon using them and bypass Galaxy Zero's effect or this card can be used to extend. This card is not searched usually and you want it late game.
    • Called By The Grave(x3)
      • Your deck does search and can be irritated by hand traps. But you can still play on even if your opponent has a hand trap. This card is just here for extra backup and support. It can also be used to distrupt your opponent on their turn.
  • Main Deck(Traps) -
    • Tachyon Transmigration(x3)
      • A negate dedicated for Galaxy-Eyes, why not run 3?
  • Extra Deck
    • Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Blade Dragon(x1)
      • This card destroys a card and can summon a Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon. So summon Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon (Effect: Steal a monster from your opponent) >> XYZ summon into Galaxy-Eyes Full Armor Photon Dragon (Effect: Destroy a monster) >> XYZ summon into Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Blade Dragon (Effect: Destroy a card). But you cant attack.
    • Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon(x1)
      • Good for XYZ summoning better XYZ monsters and can control the field with its effect.
    • Galaxy-Eyes Full Armor Photon Dragon(x1)
      • Good for destroying monsters... also has 4000 ATK
    • Galaxy-Eyes Tachyon Dragon(x1)
      • A great card for battle negation and for Tachyon Tansmigration.
    • Galaxy-Eyes Prime Photon Dragon(x1)
      • This card can gain big attack for OTKs.
    • Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord(x2)
      • The card you'll summon the most. This card is a negation and a searcher. You must run 2 minimum.
    • Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy(x1)
      • This card can make it the focus of attacks and negate spell cards which are used a lot in decks.
    • Divine Dragon Knight Felgrand(x1)
      • Great for protection or negation
    • Thunder End Dragon(x1)
      • This card should be a card of your choice. Maybe a Rank 4 or a Link monster (Borrelsword)
    • Number 97: Draglubion(x1)
      • Unless you've been restricted by card effects which have stated that you cannot summon other monsters except light monsters, this card is great as with its effect you can summon Galaxy-Eyes Prime Photon Dragon and used its effect to have 7200 ATK for OTKs. (This card replaced Galaxy-Eyes Dark Matter Dragon. RIP Dark Matter, your fellow Galaxy-Eyes XYZ monsters missing you)
    • Cyber Dragon Nova(x1)
      • To summon Cyber Dragon Infinity
    • Cyber Dragon Infinity(x1)
      • A great negation on the field.
    • Galaxy-Eyes Solflare Dragon(x2)
      • This is your Link card and you'll be summoning this card the most as well to get more XYZ monsters on the field. Its summoning effect allows you to get back a card which it mainly would be (in order of piority):
        1. Galaxy Solider (for Cyber Dragon Infinity)
        2. Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon(For its own effect). (This can also be 1st place just depends on the situation)
        3. Photon Orbital (if used as material for the Link summon or sent to the GY as a discarder) so you can use its search effect
        4. Any Photon or Galaxy monster for (its own effect again)
  • Side Deck
    • Personally, I think you should make it yourself. Not because im lazy. Look above, I did all of that typing for you. But I think the side deck should be up to the player to choose from.
The deck master is Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord as its the card which you summon the most as it is a negation and a searcher. Note: This should be taken as a guide and you should play how you want to play this deck and make changes. I personally think this is the peak at which this deck and go if playing in the current meta.

deck_excerpt: Una gran parvada de damas arpías se aproxima, que no sabrás quién te mató.
deck_description: El objetivo de este Deck es engañar al oponente trayendo a toda una parvada de damas arpías y cuando menos se lo esperen Utopía dará la estocada final.

The basic goal is to summon/spam as many normal gadget monsters as possible as quickly as possible. Summoning Platinum Gadget and Gear Gigant X to summon/search out more gadgets. Boot-up Corporal  in combination with gear charge and Machine duplication can also do well to spam out/recover gadgets from the GY. Topologic Bomber/Trisbaena can also be used as disrupting/field nukes, should things go south, with the trap monsters being good triggers for them, especially Bomber dragons effect.  This deck is very weak to Anti-Meta cards, such as banishing/anti-special summoning, do be weary of cards such as Macro cosmos.  Add spot removal as you wish.

deck_excerpt: Archfiends rise again with the help of Dark Spirits from LED5!
deck_description: Even six years after his TCG-release I'll try to build this deck around Archfiend Emperor, the First Lord of Horror and his (slightly?) better halve Archfiend Empress. But this time both of them will be supported by the recently released Curse Necrofear and the Dark Spirits from Legendary Duelists: Immortal Destiny. Foremost by the Dark Spirits - their effects allow us to special summon those heavy hitters Emperor and Empress from the grave during the damage step if your enemy attacks or if your enemy activates an effect, after you discarded them for twin twister for board clear or searching costs for the also new released Dark Spirit's Mastery spell. And don't worry about them effectless - you extend your board with the help from Archfiend Palabyrinth. The Extra Deck choices are kind of optional, because Archfiend Emperor, the First Lord of Horror only allows other fiend-type Monsters in his entourage, but Monsters like Number 49: Fortune Tune and Wind-Up Zenmaines can help you stall for a while, if you bricked a little. And with their effects they can also get off Archfiend Heiress search effect. Except Coral Dragon, which is a good card, let's you draw and you can go for higher Synchro Monsters if you want, the others are Archfiend Cards, which can later be used for the effect of Archfiend Emperor, the First Lord of Horror and Archfiend's Roar (which is also a Archfiend Card for Emperor). At the moment I have no clue what to put into the Side Deck, because in the current Meta Archfiends have not the slightest chance to compete.
Play them, love them

deck_excerpt: A deck that use Ignister and Code Talker monsters to summon Cyberse Quantum Dragon, Encode Talker, Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax and Powercode Talker a
deck_description: The main strategy of this deck is put Cyberse Quantum Dragon, Encode Talker, Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax and Powercode Talker using the support of the Code Talker and Ignister monsters, mainly the Bururu @Ignister (WIND). You need use the Cynet Codec to continuously make the moves and put all the 4 monster at the first turn (Cyberse Quantum Dragon, Encode Talker, Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax and Powercode Talker). To make this combo, you need of the Cynet Codec at start or search it with Micro Coder summoning Code Talker, next you need Summon Transcode Talker, search the Code Generator and use Transcode's effects to Summon Code Talker, next use Code Talker and Code Generator to summon Excode Talker, at this point you mainly need search the Bururu @Ignister with the Cynet Codec, then with the effect of the Code Generator send the Dotscaper to the GY and summon it with its effects, now you need Summon Inverted Code Talker at the Right of the Excode Talker activate the effect of Inverted Code Talker (chain 1) and Cynet Codec(chain 2), search the Balancer Lord and summon it with the effect of the Inverted Code Talker, now use the effect of the Balancer Lord and normal summon any monster of your hand, except the Bururu @Ignister, now with this 3 monsters Summon the Powercode Talker and search Degrade Buster, summon Degrade Buster banishing Balancer Lord and any other monster except a Level 4 (because you possibly can already have any card to summon from your GY as A.I.dle Reborn), Summon the Degrade Buster at the last Main Monster Zone of the Right side of your field, now with the Balancer Lord effect, summon the Bururu @Ignister and another level 4 monster to use this monsters to Summon the Cyberse Quantum Dragon at the Left of the Excode Talker and with the effect of the Bururu @Ignister summon the another synchro material used and use it to make Linguriboh and final use Linguriboh and Transcode Talker to summon the Crusadia Avramax at the Top of the Excode Talker. Also are able to do a Extra Link if you want. I hope you guys enjoin!

deck_name: Magical Musket Invoked Cyber Dragon Stun
deck_excerpt: Magical Musket Invoked Cyber Dragon Stun Control / OTK Ft. Experiment-XYZ (Going Second)
deck_description: Alright so the story behind this deck concept is that I had a fan named Experiment-XYZ reach out to me on discord telling me he really enjoyed playing my Musket Shaddoll list which made me feel great that I have people who appreciate my hard work for the community. He asked me, why not do a Magical Musket Invoked variant too? And I was like, yeah thats something I didn't think of that could be a really cool concept. Big shoutout to Experiment for coming up with this concept idea and allowing me to make it a reality! I love it when fans reach out to me, even just to tell me that they really like my decks. Because Aleister is an additional normal summon I only wanted to play 1 since we don't want to open many normal summons. The main target for Invocation is the Aleister link two, Aleister The Invoker of Madness. The reason for the second Invocation in the side deck is in case your opponent is playing the Invoked engine, this way having two Invocation means you can use their graveyard and their Aleister(s) to fusion summon with as fusion materials. My ratios for the Musket cards have already been explained in my previous Musket builds I have posted. The Cyber Dragon package is insane. While testing I knew that a lot of people are in fear of Chimeratech Megafleet Dragon and Chimeratech Fortress Dragon in this format because it can wipe your opponent's entire board via contact fuse if they are playing Orcust or any machine deck, or, also just wiping their extra monster zone can be enough to tear right through your opponent's board. I really like Cosmic Cyclone because it gets rid of your opponent's support cards permanently so you don't have to deal with them later on in the game, like Orcustrated Babel. My last comment I want to make is that I know the side deck is a little weird but it works. This deck is specifically for going second to break boards and Stun / OTK your opponent. But the side deck prepares you to go first as well in case they force you to go first and you know they will like if you win the die roll and you force them to go first, then game 2 they're going to make you go first since you purposely picked to go second the first time. The reason for 2 Nibiru and 1 Artifact Lancea is because I wanted to have multiple options for interruption cards since Nibiru is a hard once per turn, if you draw Nibiru and Lancea you can use both instead of being stuck with 2 Nibiru. It's more of a logical strategy that I came up with. Again, shoutout to Experiment-XYZ for helping out with this deck profile and I hope to see you guys stick around for more awesome decks!

  Gurimo runs a Warrior Deck, focused on a swarm strategy. His monsters' otherwise mediocre ATK are increased by both "The Seal of Orichalcos" and "The A. Forces". His Deck and its swarm ability is also able to take advantage of the fact that "The Seal of Orichalcos" allows him to control up to 10 monsters at once, as he places his more vulnerable monsters in the back row to prevent them from being attacked while his more defensive monsters are summoned to the front row. This strategy also can work well with "Obelisk the Tormentor", as it gives him enough monsters to Tribute for both its Summon and effect. However this strategy can also lead to his undoing, as if multiple monsters are destroyed at once, he takes even more damage, as Yugi proved.
